Man&eacute; on being on the bench vs Chelsea: &quot;It was not easy for me. It was a difficult moment. But it&rsquo;s part of football and it can happen. It's important for me to come back now. I&rsquo;m feeling very well.&quot;<br />
<br />
Man&eacute; on the injury he sustained playing for Senegal: &quot;I&rsquo;m completely recovered, yes. I&rsquo;ve been fine for around a month and that&rsquo;s why I&rsquo;ve been in training with the team and playing games.&quot;

Alexander-Arnold: &ldquo;From my point of view I&rsquo;m a lot better going forward than defensively, but I&rsquo;m a defender first &amp; foremost &amp; the most important part of that is not going forward, but how you can defend.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Alexander-Arnold: &ldquo;The staff &amp; the players around Melwood are helping me in every way they can, the sports scientists, the fitness coaches, the manager.&rdquo;

Klopp on Chelsea: &ldquo;We can always do better but in this specific game I don&rsquo;t think it was possible to do it better. The performance was absolutely okay.&ldquo;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &rdquo;If somebody wants to make a game management thing of it then that doesn&rsquo;t help because you cannot ignore the quality of the other side.&rdquo;
